snippet.textDisplay: I can't help but think it's easier to declutter when you're younger, because you've not accumulated so much stuff that actually matters. I'm in my fifties and I have a house full of "stuff", consisting of things I've inherited from loved ones, been given by loved ones, or found on my travels. I'd love to go "minimalist" but tried it once and really regret getting rid of most of the things I got rid of at the time.
